UniformGrid: change algorithm to compute hash

This is a cute bug.

Before, the has was computed with a bitwise XOR operation. This is mostly fine.
The only problem with this is that XOR is commutative: a^b = b^a, so two
different objects could produce the same hash.

Suppose we only have x0 and x1. With XOR, x0^x1 = x1^x0, which is not good. Now,
we use Python's tuple hashing method to preserve the meaning of the various
variables.
Fix: make classes that should not hashed unhashable

Before this commit, GravitationalWaves were found by identically matching the
Psi4 name in the outputs of the Multipole thorn. Now, this is more general and
we only require for the word psi4 to appear in the name. For instance, NP_Psi4
will match.
